    <text>
        <body>
            <msDesc>
                <msIdentifier>
                    <msName xml:lang="en" type="general">lectionary gospel</msName>
                    <country>Sweden</country>
                    <settlement>Stockholm</settlement>
                    <repository>Royal Library</repository>
                    <idno type="shelfmark">A787a10</idno>
                    <note>The fragment is a part from the 15th-century Russian Evangelion Aprakos
                        (Codex F, ff. 6-7, 9-10 in <ref type="bibl" target="bib:Wessél1985">Wessél
                            1985</ref>), represented by a few more leaves, kept in various
                        collections (<ref>Steensland 2003</ref>): 1. National Record Office,
                        Stockholm, Stafs. IV: 10 (Fr 11391); RA, Fr 11521 (codex 1658); 2. Royal
                        Library, Stockholm A787a15:A-B; 3. Biblioteka Adademii nauk,
                        Sankt-Petersburg 4.9.7: 2-3, 5; 6-8; 4. Royal Library, Stockholm
                        A787a10:A-B, C-D; 5. Royal Library, Stockholm A787a6; 6. The British
                        Library, Add. 34386, f.29; 7. Royal Library, Stockholm A787a23;</note>
                </msIdentifier>
                <physDesc>
                    <objectDesc form="fragment">
                        <supportDesc material="parchment">
                            <support>
                                <material>Parchment of very fine quality. Ff.1r-2v and 2r-v (2
                                    bifolia) both represents F-H, H-F sides sequences.</material>
                            </support>
                            <extent>
                                <measure unit="folia">4</measure>
                                <dimensions unit="mm" type="folia">
                                    <height>ca218</height>
                                    <width>ca310</width>
                                </dimensions>
                            </extent>
                            <foliation>Ff. 1v-8v are signed in pencil as follows: 10:A, 10: B, 10:
                                C, 10: D in the upper right-hand corner.</foliation>
                            <condition>It is a 4-leaf fragment composing to bifolia, as ff. 1 and 2
                                are detached. The parcment has retained much of its original light
                                colour and the original size. Ff. 1r, 2v, 3r and 3v have served as
                                document covers and are darker. There are number of
                                stains.</condition>
                        </supportDesc>
                        <layoutDesc>
                            <layout columns="1" writtenLines="18" ruledLines="18"/>
                        </layoutDesc>
                    </objectDesc>
                    <ink xmlns="http://www.ilit.bas.bg/repertorium/ns/3.0">Brownish for the main
                        text, red and gold for the titles and the initials.</ink>
                    <decoDesc>
                        <p>Intials <foreign xml:lang="cu">В</foreign> on f. 1r - 55 mm (5 lines) of
                            heigh, almost outside the text column, <foreign xml:lang="cu"
                                >В</foreign> on f. 2r - 45mm of height, being outside the text
                            column and discending in the lower margin, <foreign xml:lang="cu"
                                >Р</foreign> on f. 5v - 55 mm (5 lines) of heigh, outside the text
                            column, and <foreign xml:lang="cu">Р</foreign> on ff. 8v - 55 mm (5
                            lines) of heigh, outside the text column, too. These are red covered
                            with gold. The same technique is applied to the rubrics (titles)
                            introducing the coresponding readings.</p>
                    </decoDesc>
                    <bindingDesc>
                        <binding>
                            <p>Kept together with other parchment fragments (A787a)</p>
                        </binding>
                    </bindingDesc>
                    <additions type="inscriptions">
                        <list>
                            <item>
                                <locus>f. 1r</locus>
                                <quote xml:lang="sv">Lille Savolax p anno 1618 <lb/>Sigfrids
                                    Hindersons Opbördzlängds</quote>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <locus>f. 3r</locus>
                                <quote xml:lang="sv">Sigfred Henricksons Reckenskap <lb/>på Viborgz
                                    Lähn af Lille Sauolax för årh <lb/>1617, 618 och 619</quote>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </additions>
                </physDesc>
                <scribeDesc xmlns="http://www.ilit.bas.bg/repertorium/ns/3.0">
                    <scribe n="1">
                        <locus xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">1r-4v</locus>
                        <name xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">anonymous</name>
                        <scriptDesc xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" script="Cyrs" type="uncial">
                            <p>6mm high; interline space: 12mm</p>
                        </scriptDesc>
                        <scribeLang>
                            <p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Russian, Church Slavonic</p>
                        </scribeLang>
                        <respStmt xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
                            <name>Dilyana Radoslavova</name>
                            <resp>de visu</resp>
                        </respStmt>
                    </scribe>
                </scribeDesc>
                <msContents>
                    <summary>The fragment contains Luke 4.34-36, 5.1-11, 4.38-41 6.31-36, Luke
                        7.3-10, 16.19-20, 11.4-10, 9-13.</summary>
                    <filiation type="protograph">Russian</filiation>
                    <msItemStruct xml:id="ACD1">
                        <locus n="1">1r-4v</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="bg">Изборно евангелие</title>
                        <note>The text on ff. 1r-4v runs consequtively. There is another fragment
                            from the same MS (A787a6) that folls inbetween these two bifolia. There
                            is are missing folia between ff. 3 and 4.</note>
                        <filiation type="antigraph">Russian</filiation>
                        <sampleText xmlns="http://www.ilit.bas.bg/repertorium/ns/3.0" xml:lang="cu">
                            <p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="f.1r">бити на<seg
                                    rend="sup">с҃</seg> . вѣм тѧ кто еси</p>
                            <p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="f.2v">и запрѣщаа , не
                                дадѧ</p>
                            <p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="f.3r">стень л слышав же</p>
                            <p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="f.3v">нищь же нѣкто именемь
                                лазаръ .</p>
                            <p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="f.4r">и не въведи на <seg
                                    rend="sup">с҃</seg> въ искоушенїе,</p>
                            <p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="f.3v">еда подасть емоу
                                скорпїю ; аще оубо</p>
                        </sampleText>
                    </msItemStruct>
                </msContents>
